{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "ceca6c94-e705-46a8-94b8-981123fa092d",
    "name": "Tree-Crown \u2014 Full Flow (backend + compute + Airflow)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": "Exercises the whole pipeline.\n\nARCHITECTURE\n  Browser/Frontend --> our backend  /api/v1/projects/{id}/runs/analyze|finalize  (TRIGGER; returns state/job_id/run_id/mode)\n  our backend --> Airflow REST       /api/v1/dags/{dag}/dagRuns                   (starts the DAG)\n  Airflow DAG --> our backend         /api/v1/compute/analyze|finalize            (COMPUTE; returns asset_id/version/hosting_platform)\n\nSo asset_id/version/hosting_platform come ONLY from /compute/* (folder 3), not from the /runs/* trigger.\n\nRECOMMENDED ORDER\n  0 Health -> 1 Setup (create + upload ortho) -> then either:\n    A) Trigger path (folder 2): runs/analyze, poll runs/status, GET clustering, submit labels (folder 4), runs/finalize, results; OR\n    B) Compute path (folder 3): call /compute/analyze and /compute/finalize directly to see the STACD response the DAG receives.\n\nNOTE: /compute/* run the REAL pipeline synchronously (minutes). The project must have an ortho (for analyze) and submitted labels + LABELS_SUBMITTED state (for finalize).\nSet variables under the collection's Variables tab. apiKey/computeToken can be blank if the server has no auth set."
  },
